<subSubSection id="3DFBEC767A470A20F7570F2F64D6BE7F" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" type="range">
<paragraph id="3C17EC2FBD89A8F0550AD8401382FA53" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Range.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0145902ABBE77E066428B922F30D611E" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">CANADA: Alberta, British Columbia, Manitoba (sw), Northwest Territories (sw), Ontario (Manitoulin Island), Quebec (Gaspe Peninsula), Saskatchewan, Yukon (s). UNITED STATES: Alaska (se interior border), Arizona (n), California, Colorado, Idaho, Montana, North Dakota, Nevada, New Mexico (n), Oregon, South Dakota (w), Utah, Washington, Wyoming, with outlying populations in Nebraska (w), Oklahoma (panhandle), Michigan (Isle Royal) and sporadic in Illinois and Maine, Massachusetts.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D15ED657075C1484A5A66F0690601204" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">
The geographic range of 
<taxonomicName id="9C7C63B7C9CA83983C07DC95A74FAB72" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. secunda" order="Poales" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="secunda">
<emphasis id="3F87F84DA05E2CE7628AEDF09975AB13" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">P. secunda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in North America north of Mexico is mapped in Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B18334148C4D8C1CFE812BCDFDCC3E45" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Distribution of Poa secunda subspecies in North America: subsp. secunda (yellow); subsp. juncifolia (blue)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.110.27750.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/240277" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">2</figureCitation>
. Subspecies 
<taxonomicName id="C5A1901060ECE9176B2A253250F1ED80" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" subspecies="secunda">
<emphasis id="A6C7C033502E5F297D7DCED0BD224113" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">secunda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs throughout the species range and also reaches into Baja California Norte, Mexico (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="50CF6007F2C524B5DD2261D17D99CAF3" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Distribution of Poa secunda subspecies in North America: subsp. secunda (yellow); subsp. juncifolia (blue)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.110.27750.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/240277" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">2A</figureCitation>
). The range of subspecies 
<taxonomicName id="DAB3659477E5E854E786006256D11996" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" subspecies="juncifolia">juncifolia</taxonomicName>
is almost completely within that of subsp. 
<taxonomicName id="6F1C5247691A9657474E03ADF2E9DB8E" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="P." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" subspecies="secunda">
<emphasis id="B71924AB9CBD3C8DFA32B1751A686D85" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">secunda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, except for several scattered localities in Arizona, New Mexico and Nebraska; it is absent from Mexico and mostly absent from the Pacific Coast and coastal mountains (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="3DB695CE776A55785AE3FD765B54F4E3" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Distribution of Poa secunda subspecies in North America: subsp. secunda (yellow); subsp. juncifolia (blue)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.110.27750.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/240277" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">2B</figureCitation>
). The ranges of varieties are broadly overlapping within their subspecies. Both subspecies have disjunct populations in the Patagonian Andes of Argentina and Chile.
</paragraph>
